## 3. Backend Architecture

### 3.1 `app.js` — Express Application

The core Express app is assembled here with full middleware stack:

| Middleware | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `helmet()` | HTTP security headers |
| `cors()` | Whitelist-based CORS (FRONTEND_URL + localhost) |
| `mongo-sanitize` | NoSQL injection prevention |
| `express.json()` | JSON body parsing (global, 10kb limit) |
| `express.raw()` | Raw buffer for webhook routes (PayPal/Cashfree signature verification) |
| `morgan` | HTTP request logging |
| `Sentry` | Error monitoring (requestHandler + errorHandler) |
| `rateLimit` | Per-endpoint granular rate limiting |
| `timingMiddleware` | Performance timing headers on responses |

**Public Routes (no auth required):**
- `GET /api/v1/platform-stats` — aggregated counts (tools, categories, active trials), Redis-cached 5 min
- `GET /api/v1/featured` — sponsored tool listings, Redis-cached, feature-flagged
- `GET /api/v1/tools` — paginated tool listing with filters
- `GET /api/v1/tools/search` — Algolia search proxy
- `GET /api/v1/tools/:slug` — individual tool detail
- `GET /api/v1/categories` — all categories

**Authenticated Routes:**
- `/api/v1/payment/*` — PayPal + Cashfree order creation/capture/webhooks
- `/api/v1/users/*` — user profile, subscription, favorites, reviews
- `/api/v1/tools` (POST/PUT/DELETE) — admin tool management
- `/api/v1/admin/*` — admin dashboard, tool approval, revenue, vendor claims

**SEO/Programmatic Routes:**
- `GET /api/v1/seo/alternatives/:slug` — "X alternatives" pages
- `GET /api/v1/seo/best-tools/:role` — "Best AI tools for [role]" pages
- `GET /api/v1/sitemap.xml` — auto-generated XML sitemap

### 3.2 `server.js` — Bootstrap & Cron Startup

On startup, the server:
1. Connects to MongoDB
2. Connects to Redis
3. Registers Sentry
4. Starts HTTP server
5. Launches all cron jobs in sequence:
   - `startTrialCron()` — daily trial lifecycle management
   - `startWinBackCron()` — churn win-back email sequences
   - `startEnrichmentCron()` — daily trending score recompute
   - `startDiscoveryScheduler()` — every 4h crawler + Groq enrichment

